OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1782197284
OL,3,CWhat are my rights if my workplace is
OL,4,Ctoo hot?
OL,6,FThe HSE says employers are responsible
OL,7,Ffor maintaining "thermal comfort",
OL,8,Falthough there is no fixed legal
OL,9,Ftemperature limit.
OL,11,FSome employers choose to stop work
OL,12,Fduring extreme heat.
OL,14,FThey must also carry out risk
OL,15,Fassessments before assigning work.
OL,17,FHow can employers protect workers?
OL,19,FThere are practical steps employers
OL,20,Fcan take to protect workers in very
OL,21,Fhigh or very low temperatures.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/10
