OL,3,CWhat are my rights if my workplace is
OL,4,Ctoo hot?
OL,6,FWhat about travelling to work in
OL,7,Fextreme heat?
OL,9,FEmployers' responsibilities can extend
OL,10,Fbeyond the workplace if extreme
OL,11,Ftemperatures create health and safety
OL,12,Frisks during commuting.
OL,14,FUnder Section 44 of the Employment
OL,15,FRights Act 1996, workers can remove
OL,16,Fthemselves from situations they
OL,17,Freasonably believe pose a "serious and
OL,18,Fimminent danger".
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
