PN,31909
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1782197284
OL,3,CWhat are my rights if my workplace is
OL,4,Ctoo hot?
OL,6,FHowever, this protection applies to
OL,7,Fimmediate safety risks rather than
OL,8,Fgeneral discomfort.
OL,10,FAre unions calling for stronger
OL,11,Fprotections?
OL,13,FThe Trade Union Congress (TUC) and
OL,14,FUNISON are both calling for a legal
OL,15,Fmaximum indoor working temperature of
OL,16,F30C, or 27C for strenuous work.
OL,18,FThey say temperatures above 24C should
OL,19,Fbe reduced where possible, or action
OL,20,Ftaken if workers feel uncomfortable.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/10
